786,TCP,NFS-Mountd,storage,dst,internal,NFS mountd negotiation port (Proxmox <-> TrueNAS NFS mounts)
813,TCP,NFS-Aux,storage,dst,internal,NFS auxiliary (statd or lockd range seen in Proxmox/TrueNAS traffic)
741,TCP,NFS-Aux,storage,dst,internal,NFS auxiliary port seen in Proxmox/TrueNAS traffic
747,TCP,NFS-Aux,storage,dst,internal,NFS auxiliary port seen in Proxmox/TrueNAS traffic
2049,TCP,NFS,storage,dst,internal,NFS data plane (already in Vector map - duplicate entry for registry completeness)
2380,TCP,etcd-Peer,k8s,dst,internal,etcd peer replication between k8s control-plane nodes
3300,TCP,Ceph-Monitor,storage,dst,internal,Ceph monitor messenger v2 (msgr2) — rook-ceph-mon pods
6800,TCP,Ceph-OSD,storage,dst,internal,Ceph OSD messenger v2 base port
6801,TCP,Ceph-OSD,storage,dst,internal,Ceph OSD messenger v2 (rook-ceph OSD port range)
6802,TCP,Ceph-OSD,storage,dst,internal,Ceph OSD messenger v2 (rook-ceph OSD port range)
6803,TCP,Ceph-OSD,storage,dst,internal,Ceph OSD messenger v2 (rook-ceph OSD port range)
6804,TCP,Ceph-OSD,storage,dst,internal,Ceph OSD messenger v2 (rook-ceph OSD port range)
6808,TCP,Ceph-Manager,storage,dst,internal,Ceph MGR messenger v2 (rook-ceph-mgr)
# --- Note: Ceph OSD replication uses ephemeral dst_ports (30000-60000 range) ---
# These flows are identified by dst_k8s_workload pattern in Phase 3 VRL extension,
# not by port number. Do not attempt to list the ephemeral ports here.
